    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 21-SI SERIES - BEARING REPLACEMENT - SRE HOUSING BEARING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="2">
        <title>SRE HOUSING BEARING</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <para>Check bearing in SRE housing. Bearings are permanently lubricated; do not add grease. If bearing is
                dry or damaged, replace bearing.
            </para>
            <para>If bearing is being replaced without removing brushes from SRE housing, use brush pin to hold brushes
                in retracted position while bearing is removed.
            </para>
            <para>Remove bearing, using tube slightly smaller than the opening in the SRE housing and pressing bearing
                through to inside of housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0801718">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0801718" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0801718" filename="../figg08/G0801718.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Removing SRE Bearing</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HAMMER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TUBE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SRE BEARING</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. SRE HOUSING</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0801719">Figure 19</hotlnk>
                for Item numbers in parentheses.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0801719" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0801719" filename="../figg08/G0801719.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>sre Bearing Installation</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SRE HOUSING</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SRE BEARING</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. TUBE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. HAMMER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Install SRE housing bearing (Item 2) into SRE housing (Item 1). Use thin-wall socket or tube (Item 3)
                slightly smaller than hole in SRE housing; press bearing in from outside. Position bearing flush with
                outside lip of SRE housing.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
